                    "R2aExhibit": {
                        "ProjectMissionDescription": {
                            "val": "Tactical Mission Command (TMC) is a portfolio of products and services that enable commanders and their staff with collaborative environment, planning tools, and Common Operation Picture (COP) management and other maneuver functional tools.  The overarching capability includes above platform level user-defined COP with integrated Command and Control (C2) and Situational Awareness (SA), map-centric collaboration, Army Mission Command System and other enabling system interoperability, data management and enterprise services. Products include:\n\nCommand Web is a set of modular software widgets served up over the web providing engineering functionality. Improved supportability and ease-of-use in robust network environments.\n\nTactical Server Infrastructure (TSI) provides the network available services critical to ensuring system and software can transmit the network effectively.  Additionally, TSI serves as the hosting platform for many other enabling software systems, as well as multiple Warfighter Functional Area Applications (WFAs) such as Intel, Air Missile Defense Workstations and Fires gateway, providing efficiencies in the Command Post via decreased size, weight and power.\n\nWAVE is the voice of the internet protocol common voice solution for the CPOF portfolio of programs.  It provides real-time voice interoperability between radios, intercom and other previously fielded technologies in support of the Commander's update briefing and other Mission Command tasks."
                        },
